value.title: Twitter flags Trump tweets complaining of 'ballot dumps'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday hit out at what he described as “surprise ballot dumps” as ballot counts in the Rust Belt show his lead shrinking in those states -- a claim that was swiftly labeled as "misleading" by Twitter.

value.title: Totals from Milwaukee, Kenosha and Green Bay push Biden to a 20,000 vote lead in Wisconsin
value.excerpt: Trump did worse in much of Milwaukee and Madison than he did four years ago, but did a little better in much of northern and central Wisconsin.

value.title: Media and polls 'hyper-judgmental' of Trump supporters: Candace Owens
value.excerpt: Conservative activist Candace Owens slammed the media and pollsters for once again failing to accurately predict the presidential election.

value.title: AOC sounds alarm over Latino turnout for Biden
value.excerpt: Democratic U.S. Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez vented her frustrations over lackluster Democratic turnout among Latinos Tuesday evening.

value.title: Pennsylvania's Democratic governor calls Trump remarks 'partisan attack'
value.excerpt: Pennsylvania's Democratic Governor Tom Wolf on Wednesday called President Donald Trump's unsubstantiated claim about fraud in the U.S. presidential election a "partisan attack", and said his state was working hard to count more than 1 million mail-in ballots.

value.title: Kid Rock responds to Lady Gaga's Biden endorsement, shows 'what camo is really worn for'
value.excerpt: Kid Rock seemed to have a go at Lady Gaga on Tuesday, days after the pop star went viral with her own pro-Joe Biden video.

value.title: Trump narrows gap in heavily Latino Texas county that Clinton won by 79%
value.excerpt: President Trump has made up a lot of ground in Starr County, Texas, since 2016 in what once a Democratic stronghold, according to results from the Texas Secretary of State's Office.

value.title: RNC speaker Kim Klacik falls short in House bid despite viral campaign ad, Trump support
value.excerpt: Republican newcomer Kim Klacik fell short on Election Day in her bid to win a U.S. House seat in a Maryland district that includes inner-city Baltimore.

value.title: Republican Lindsey Graham defeats well-funded Democratic challenger Jaime Harrison in South Carolina
value.excerpt: South Carolina Republican Sen. Lindsey Graham will return to the Senate for a fourth term after defeating Democratic challenger Jaime Harrison.

value.title: Ex-ESPN host Jemele Hill says 'it's on White people' if Trump wins reelection: 'No one else'
value.excerpt: ESPN host Jemele Hill declared Tuesday that only White people are to blame if President Trump defeats Democratic nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Latest Election Day updates: Trump has a commanding lead in Florida
value.excerpt: Our live coverage of Election Day includes updates on voter turnout, the latest on Trump and Biden, and news from polling places around Florida.

value.title: Biden surrogate Coons says campaign is 'cautiously optimistic' about election results
value.excerpt: The Biden campaign is "cautiously optimistic" heading into election night and believes it will ultimately come out ahead in the key battleground of Pennsylvania, one of its surrogates told Fox News.

value.title: Trump Ally Tweets Misleading Images of Philadelphia Voting
value.excerpt: Early Tuesday, a Trump campaign official posted an unfounded suggestion on Twitter that Democrats were illegally campaigning at a voting site in Philadelphia. Twitter labeled the tweet “misleading” and later “manipulated,

value.title: Indian village where Kamala Harris' grandfather was born prays for her win
value.excerpt: People gathered Tuesday in a village in India that was once home to the forebears of D Kamala Harris to pray for her ticket's victory in the U.S. presidential election, Reuters news agency reported .

value.title: Ex-Gov. and Ex-Inmate Rod Blagojevich Votes, Trump Having Commuted Sentence
value.excerpt: Former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich cast his first ballot Tuesday since President Trump [earlier this year]( commuted his 14-year sentence for multiple corruption crimes. He voted a split ticket. “It

value.title: Barbara Res helped build Trump Tower. She says she saw Donald Trump ignore experts and disrespect employees in her 18 years working with him.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump has long displayed certain behaviors, says Barbara Res, whose new book "Tower of Lies" recounts almost 2 decades of working with him.

value.title: Colorado Sen. Michael Bennet not interested in being Biden's education secretary
value.excerpt: Colorado’s senior Democratic senator has said he would not be interested in serving as education secretary under a prospective Joe Biden’s administration, despite his background in public education.

value.title: CNN's Don Lemon hits network for airing Trump's 'propaganda' visit to RNC office
value.excerpt: CNN anchor Don Lemon questioned the judgment of his own network Tuesday after it broadcast remarks President Trump made during his visit to a Republican National Committee office.

value.title: Trump mistakenly introduced the rapper Lil Pump as 'Little Pimp' at his final campaign rally
value.excerpt: One of the big superstars of the world, Little Pimp!' said President Trump as he introduced the rapper Lil Pump.

value.title: In St. Petersburg, Fla., Trump's Character Is in Focus
value.excerpt: With millions of Floridians having already voted, the Election Day line quickly diminished outside the largest polling location in St. Petersburg, Fla. The city resides in Pinellas County, one of the bellwether counties in the country's largest battleground state.

value.title: Kamala Harris' husband declares Ohio a 'blue state' during Election Day visit to Columbus
value.excerpt: Underscoring the Democrats' attempt to steal battleground Ohio from Donald Trump - who won the state in 2016 - Doug Emhoff rallies Biden supporters.

value.title: Trump thanks campaign staffers, predicts 'incredible night': 'Tremendous group of people'
value.excerpt: The president spoke for a time to campaign staff and answered questions from the media before hitting the road again.

value.title: 'Winning is easy. Losing is never easy': Trump stops by RNC office in Virginia
value.excerpt: Donald Trump said he is not thinking about an acceptance or a concession speech when he stopped at the Republican National Committee Headquarters.

value.title: In the Minneapolis neighborhood where George Floyd died, voters disagree with Biden on policing. But they're voting for him anyway.
value.excerpt: Voters in Powderhorn Park told Insider they think President Donald Trump is even worse, so they voted for Joe Biden despite their reservations.

value.title: Kamala Harris in Detroit to rally Election Day support: 'Have faith in the American people'
value.excerpt: Harris encouraged voters to trust their neighbors and the electoral process before canvassing throughout metro Detroit.
